title: Print, "Raid on a Sand-Swallow Colony - "How Many Eggs?" from Harper's Weekly, June 13, 1874, p. 496.", 1874
signed:
Signed on block with initials, lower right: W.H.
Signed on beach shrub, lower left: Lagarde
inscribed: Caption: Raid on a Sand-Swallow Colony-"How Many Eggs?"-(Drawn by Winslow Homer.)
creditline: Gift of John Goldsmith Phillips, Jr.
description: Four boys stealing eggs from sand swallows' nests.  At top left, one boy is sitting on the bluff stealing eggs, while three boys climb the dune, one is pulling on an old shirt that the boys are using to collect eggs.

tombstone.epitaph: Print, "Raid on a Sand-Swallow Colony - "How Many Eggs?" from Harper's Weekly, June 13, 1874, p. 496.", 1874.Wood engraving on paper. Gift of John Goldsmith Phillips, Jr.. 1947-4-31.
